way with the problems it brings to EQ.<br>
<br>
It's simple.  If 50%(or some other appropriate percentage) or more of a mob's life is taken by manaburn(and this counts all manaburns) then it leaves no corpse and gives no exp.  <br>
<br>
Small guilds with one or two manaburn enabled wizards would still be able to help out in Kunark encounter.  Wait until that dragon hits 49%, and burn away.<br>
<br>
It would still be useful to take down normal mobs immediately, when you absolutely positively have to stop that CHing cleric mob.<br>
<br>
The only thing that would change is that 'Team Manaburn' would be unable to farm dragons for loot.<br>
<br>
All the legitimate(to me, at least) uses of manaburn are preserved.<br>
<br>
Perhaps in compensation, have manaburn scale slightly based on a mob's total HP.  Nothing astronomical, maybe 25% higher or so on mobs with hundreds of thousands of hitpoints.<br>
<br>
Are there any ramifications of this I missed?  Any suggestions?  While I know changing manaburn is not a subject popular among most wizards, it seems that Verant has a tendency to wildly overcompensate whenever they perceive a problem in balance.  So, it's better that sensible changes to submitted to them, before VI decides to make Manaburn castable only on moss snakes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 661<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 2:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sensible Manaburn change, and a request for comments</span><hr size=1> 7 to 9k damage on a full bar of mana for a level 60 wizard is weak enough.  I can see them nerfing CRIT ability on manaburn, but to eliminate the ability to use manaburn on ANY mob below a certain level is pathetic.  What, I can't kill a 7k mob once every now and then because they are worried?  How about a group of melees who take down a Kunark dragon in under a minute with their Velious weapons?  Can we get a nerf for them too, like no weapon that's more powerful than what's in Kunark can work in Kunark zones?<br>
Yea, let's nerf priceless/primal armor, and in Kunark zones, all melees get at most a 30 percent haste total, regardless of upgrades.<br>
